<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFCB6573FF4345CCFDFDC5A8" blockId="15.[151,602,1191,1218]" box="[151,602,1191,1218]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D6EFFCB6573FF3D45C3FDFDC5A8" authority="Marion, 1956" authorityName="Marion" authorityYear="1956" box="[233,602,1191,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Argyrophorodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEAFFFFCB6573FF3D45C3FE0BC5AB" bold="true" box="[233,428,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Argyrophorodes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B1CFFCB6573FE6F45CCFDFDC5A8" author="Marion" box="[443,602,1192,1218]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref43041" refString="Marion,. (1956) Naturaliste malagache 8." type="book" year="1956">Marion, 1956</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3706566FFCB6573FF43458BFD3EC4B4" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFCB6573FF43458BFD77C46C" blockId="15.[151,1436,1262,1502]" box="[151,720,1262,1287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<typeStatus id="54D1884FFFCB6573FF43458BFF69C46D" box="[151,206,1263,1287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D6EFFCB6573FEF9458AFD6BC46C" authority="Mabille, 1880" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1880" box="[301,716,1262,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Nymphula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteivittalis">
<emphasis id="B91EEAFFFFCB6573FEF9458AFD82C46C" box="[301,549,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Nymphula luteivittalis</emphasis>
Mabille, 1880
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFCB6573FF134476FCDCC418" blockId="15.[151,1436,1262,1502]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
A genus of fewer than ten species, all described hitherto from 
<collectingCountry id="F37D767DFFCB6573FC6A4476FBE0C440" box="[958,1095,1298,1322]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. One of the chief characters described by Marion occurs only in the males, but only females have been found in Africa; however the long maxillary palpus and wing pattern suggest this generic placement.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFCB6573FF13441AFD3EC4B4" blockId="15.[151,1436,1262,1502]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The corpus bursae of the female genitalia is without signa. No males of the African species have been available for study. Although there are over 
<specimenCount id="9D6CFD64FFCB6573FD4244C6FC88C4D0" box="[662,815,1442,1466]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="generic">30 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D6EFFCB6573FC8344C7FC68C4D1" authority="Published, 2012" authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2012" box="[855,975,1443,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Argyrophorodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angolensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91EEAFFFFCB6573FC8344C7FC68C4D1" box="[855,975,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">angolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91EEAFFFFCB6573FC0344C7FBBFC4D1" bold="true" box="[983,1048,1443,1467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22D5784FFCB6573FC0344C7FBBFC4D1" box="[983,1048,1443,1467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the lack of males raises questions about whether they might be parthenogenetic.
</paragraph>
